metadata.name: Snowflake #264
metadata.description:
This snowflake is created using a cellular automaton in a hexagonal grid. 

Each tile can be in a binary state of either being free or frozen. The next state is determined by assigning a random probability of freezing and thawing to each possible combination of frozen/free neighbouring tiles.

Some Snowflakes will die, some will find a stable state, some will loop but most of them will keep going forever.

Press space to pause/unpause.

For Free. 

Merry Christmas!

metadata.name: Urbs #116
metadata.description:
Our civilization is inseparable from our cities, and this project studies what the code, using only rectangles, circles and some noise, can tell us about the ones we currently inhabit or the future ones we may build on Earth or somewhere beyond.

We may plan them orderly, but they often become chaotic due to the nature of humans and the cosmos itself, and these same forces can lead to decay, decommissioning or destruction

However, how high or low we go largely depends on us.

Features: Plan & Order, Entropy & Resistance, Decay & Disintegration plus, there are numerous variations in palettes, city designs, perspective, motion effects, project sizes, building types, lighting…

Hope that you will enjoy your mint. 
Thank you for support!

Press 's' to save the canvas or ‘4’ (or ‘H’) for a 4x HD image resolution PNG. 
Vanilla 2D p5js without additional libraries created with love for code and generative art. @Qotonana, April 2024

metadata.name: (Anti)thesis #45
metadata.description:
This is my first fxhash work. It is a generative, deterministic, object-oriented algorithm written entirely in p5.js. With the exception of two very rare background colours, the colour palettes are not pre-selected but entirely generated using your transaction hash.

The algorithm plays on the concept of Antithesis (/ænˈtɪθəsɪs/ - direct contrast; opposition) by using opposing forces to generate tension (and occasional calm) between forms on the page and the spaces in between. Inspiration was also drawn from works and advice from the great Daniel Catt (@revdancatt).

I hope you like it. Thanks for your support.
tallzy

metadata.name: Strange Lands #34
metadata.description:
Strange lands #fxhashturnsone

What is so interesting about a map tile? 

This work is delving into that shape, how a few different lines can create a tiny world. Heavily influenced by Matt DesLauriers work 'Subscapes' which is one of my favorite on-chain projects and the best instance of this composition. My take is a bit less refined and more abstract.

HBD Fxhash, and many more 🎂🍻.

Made of around 14kb of JS. No libraries. 

All tez to charity.

metadata.name: (DE)STRUCTURAL #95
metadata.description:
"Reserve a spot for your family and loved ones in our brand new *floating* high rise condominiums. Leave the dirty air of Level-1 behind! Discount of 200'000'000 credits applicable is you already own any of our apartments in another sector."

Like with my previous works, each variation starts as an empty black canvas in the depth of your [CALCULATING MACHINE]. With your [UNIQUE PURCHASE TRANSACTION RECEIPT] specially constructed AI engineers start to envision a condominium that is perfect just for you! Utilizing both the [CENTRAL PROCESSING UNIT] and [GRAPHICS PROCESSING UNIT] the blueprints materialize in front of your [ORGANS OF VISION OR OF LIGHT SENSITIVITY]. Everything is procedurally generated taking in hundreds of randomized parameters bound to specific rules of construction.

Orbit: mouse [PRIMARY] button.
Pan: mouse [SECONDARY] button.
Zoom: mouse [GYRATION DISC].
Cycle light intensity levels: [B]

metadata.name: We Care...Duck #9
metadata.description:
We are not the only inhabitants of the earth,

The earth does not belong only to humans

From the seas to the deserts,animals face the ongoing threat of cruelty and abuse. Bears are captured and forced to fight dogs. Marine mammals, such as whales and dolphins, get trapped in discarded fishing gear. Wild animals are traded as exotic pets.

We should end the needless suffering of animals.
We should influence decision makers to put animals on the global agenda.
We should help the world see how important animals are to all of us.
We inspire people to change animals’ lives for the better.
We should move the world to protect animals.

------------------


Duck is the common name for numerous species of waterfowl in the family Anatidae. Ducks are generally smaller and shorter-necked than swans and geese, which are members of the same family. Divided among several subfamilies, they are a form taxon; they do not represent a monophyletic group (the group of all descendants of a single common ancestral species), since swans and geese are not considered ducks. Ducks are mostly aquatic birds, and may be found in both fresh water and sea water.

Ducks are sometimes confused with several types of unrelated water birds with similar forms, such as loons or divers, grebes, gallinules and coots.

metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #199
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.
